@thanasisk 

> `INFO[0000] None of the challenges sent by server (127.0.0.1) are supported, trying an unauthenticated request anyway`

Hum, that 127.0.0.1 is supposed to be a list of server-accepted authentication types. Can you capture the full HTTP response headers of the access to the registry’s `/v2/` URL, please? The output of `curl -iL https://$registry/v2/` , or something like that, might be a start.
